  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A previously healthy 28-year-old man presents to the emergency department with fever and a painful rash that began on his genitals and perianal area and spread to his torso and face over the last week. He reports recent sexual contact with a male partner who developed a similar rash two weeks ago. Vital signs are: P, 92; BP, 128/84; T, 38.7°C (101.7°F). Physical examination reveals a rash as shown, as well as generalized lymphadenopathy. Laboratory studies show: WBC 12,500/μL, ALT 68 U/L, AST 74 U/L. What is the most appropriate next step in management?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Obtain blood cultures and start empiric IV ceftriaxone and vancomycin"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Prescribe topical terbinafine and recommend follow-up with the primary care physician"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Order HSV serology and arrange follow-up with the STI clinic"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Isolate the patient and swab a lesion for viral PCR testing"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Administer IV acyclovir and consult internal medicine"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 4,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7l04yT&anker=Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-learningcard-id=\"7l04yT\" data-anker=\"Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-sememe-id=\"kn0mtg\">Blood cultures</a> and empiric <span data-sememe-id=\"7WW4540\">broad-spectrum antibiotics</span> would be appropriate for suspected <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xm0E3g&anker=Zb3de189fac0d57eac5b7798e127a5e19\" data-learningcard-id=\"xm0E3g\" data-anker=\"Zb3de189fac0d57eac5b7798e127a5e19\" data-sememe-id=\"YNan-k\">sepsis</a> or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ZR0Zlf&anker=Z4738db1ddf5a4ab230fa84e70829a39b\" data-learningcard-id=\"ZR0Zlf\" data-anker=\"Z4738db1ddf5a4ab230fa84e70829a39b\" data-section-id=\"gKaFfl\" data-sememe-id=\"2IbTXE\">meningococcemia</a>, which can present with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j50_Pg&anker=Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-learningcard-id=\"j50_Pg\" data-anker=\"Za5de83449ff6a749e6c1348b93b1f3b1\" data-sememe-id=\"CL0q-g\">fever</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Su0yq3&anker=Z94dd620719b07efc1500cb2ec985505a\" data-learningcard-id=\"Su0yq3\" data-anker=\"Z94dd620719b07efc1500cb2ec985505a\">rash</a>. However, this patient's well-circumscribed <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z7c5fd3823051fa560edec27fe227985f\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z7c5fd3823051fa560edec27fe227985f\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"tCaXF5\">vesicular lesions</a> that began in the genital area and spread <span data-sememe-id=\"gj0F-f\">centrifugally</span> are inconsistent with bacterial infections, which typically cause <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z407bfee1be646713a1d7c946d9f4d4f0\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z407bfee1be646713a1d7c946d9f4d4f0\" data-section-id=\"0vXeA-\" data-sememe-id=\"yCadu5\">petechial</a> or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Zc8dd5ca664223e28e1b5912fb7e2b52b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Zc8dd5ca664223e28e1b5912fb7e2b52b\" data-section-id=\"0vXeA-\" data-sememe-id=\"BCaz85\">purpuric</a> rashes, usually in the extremities. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7l04yT&anker=Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-learningcard-id=\"7l04yT\" data-anker=\"Zbbc1ac48182c8850d109967ff3d2e390\" data-sememe-id=\"kn0mtg\">Blood cultures</a> would be unlikely to yield positive results in this patient, who likely has a viral underlying cause.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>Topical <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=6m0jgg&anker=Z94404554781be4122edebfc0e6fa8c13\" data-learningcard-id=\"6m0jgg\" data-anker=\"Z94404554781be4122edebfc0e6fa8c13\">antifungal</a> therapy and outpatient management would be appropriate for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Hf0Kn2&anker=Zb858d91eafc2df28efbe47843c686b75\" data-learningcard-id=\"Hf0Kn2\" data-anker=\"Zb858d91eafc2df28efbe47843c686b75\" data-section-id=\"ISdYap0\" data-sememe-id=\"eLax9O\">tinea corporis</a>, which can cause spreading <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=W60PPS&anker=Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\" data-learningcard-id=\"W60PPS\" data-anker=\"Z84ffaf83e57bb0cc8eb7c50bbc266078\">skin</a> lesions. However, the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z7c5fd3823051fa560edec27fe227985f\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z7c5fd3823051fa560edec27fe227985f\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"tCaXF5\">vesicular</a> appearance of this patient's <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Su0yq3&anker=Z94dd620719b07efc1500cb2ec985505a\" data-learningcard-id=\"Su0yq3\" data-anker=\"Z94dd620719b07efc1500cb2ec985505a\">rash</a> is inconsistent with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=EF08P3&anker=Z4da552dd5059fd9bf0789e49b6bb6de2\" data-learningcard-id=\"EF08P3\" data-anker=\"Z4da552dd5059fd9bf0789e49b6bb6de2\">fungal infections</a>, which typically present as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4k03LT&anker=Z51448f8db1319ab6162a448374ac15d9\" data-learningcard-id=\"4k03LT\" data-anker=\"Z51448f8db1319ab6162a448374ac15d9\" data-section-id=\"o0b0SH\">scaling</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z2402afe504766ef84f64acad4aaea47b\" data-section-id=\"0vXeA-\" data-sememe-id=\"3wYSir\">erythematous</a> <span data-sememe-id=\"0wYehr\">plaques</span>. Additionally, this patient's systemic symptoms, laboratory abnormalities, and epidemiological <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ps0LDh&anker=Zbc0d0ff153bc5c7a27589815d0c842fd\" data-learningcard-id=\"ps0LDh\" data-anker=\"Zbc0d0ff153bc5c7a27589815d0c842fd\" data-section-id=\"FfWgLk0\" data-sememe-id=\"b31HSg0\">risk factors</a> warrant more urgent management than outpatient follow-up.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>Testing for <span data-sememe-id=\"yE1dyi0\">Herpes simplex virus</span> (<span data-sememe-id=\"yE1dyi0\">HSV</span>) and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=IM0YJg&anker=Za2185673cc278f4e363afb0a09c68c52\" data-learningcard-id=\"IM0YJg\" data-anker=\"Za2185673cc278f4e363afb0a09c68c52\" data-sememe-id=\"Go0BWS\">STI</a> clinic follow-up would be appropriate for suspected <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mL0Vyg&anker=Z38e200a987479ddb4830b44939db16bd\" data-learningcard-id=\"mL0Vyg\" data-anker=\"Z38e200a987479ddb4830b44939db16bd\" data-section-id=\"ifcJNb0\" data-sememe-id=\"oya0TM\">genital herpes</a>, which can present with painful <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z7c5fd3823051fa560edec27fe227985f\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z7c5fd3823051fa560edec27fe227985f\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"tCaXF5\">vesicular lesions</a> in the genital area. However, this patient's <span data-sememe-id=\"gj0F-f\">centrifugal</span> spread pattern and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=iL0Jxg&anker=Z7b0bf382e960f8be4f9fccafce5ff227\" data-learningcard-id=\"iL0Jxg\" data-anker=\"Z7b0bf382e960f8be4f9fccafce5ff227\" data-section-id=\"2YWToP0\" data-sememe-id=\"66cjNW0\">generalized lymphadenopathy</a> are inconsistent with simple genital <span data-sememe-id=\"yE1dyi0\">HSV</span>, which typically remains localized. Additionally, <span data-sememe-id=\"yE1dyi0\">HSV</span> <span data-sememe-id=\"JkbsKF\">serology</span> would not provide immediate diagnostic information for acute infection; viral <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=gp0FKS&anker=Z3a8f5e31aa62111944442fd86660cc27\" data-learningcard-id=\"gp0FKS\" data-anker=\"Z3a8f5e31aa62111944442fd86660cc27\" data-section-id=\"G9cBKe0\" data-sememe-id=\"RfYlNo\">PCR</a> from a lesion is preferred. Outpatient follow-up would also be inappropriate for this patient, who warrants more urgent evaluation and <span data-sememe-id=\"pD1L2Q0\">public health</span> measures given their clinical presentation and risk. Disseminated <span data-sememe-id=\"yE1dyi0\">HSV</span> might be a possibility, but it is managed differently.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) CORRECT:</h4>Correct – This immunocompetent patient's clinical presentation of well-circumscribed <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z7c5fd3823051fa560edec27fe227985f\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z7c5fd3823051fa560edec27fe227985f\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"tCaXF5\">vesicular lesions</a>, <span data-sememe-id=\"gj0F-f\">centrifugal</span> spread pattern, systemic symptoms, and recent close contact with someone who had a similar <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Su0yq3&anker=Z94dd620719b07efc1500cb2ec985505a\" data-learningcard-id=\"Su0yq3\" data-anker=\"Z94dd620719b07efc1500cb2ec985505a\">rash</a> is consistent with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=1G02yh&anker=Ze402dff64227ad6c4820695274ada3bb\" data-learningcard-id=\"1G02yh\" data-anker=\"Ze402dff64227ad6c4820695274ada3bb\" data-sememe-id=\"QIWuc50\">mpox</a> infection. Immediate isolation is essential as patients remain contagious until all lesions heal. A lesion swab for viral <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=gp0FKS&anker=Z3a8f5e31aa62111944442fd86660cc27\" data-learningcard-id=\"gp0FKS\" data-anker=\"Z3a8f5e31aa62111944442fd86660cc27\" data-section-id=\"G9cBKe0\" data-sememe-id=\"RfYlNo\">PCR</a> testing will provide a definitive diagnosis. Infectious disease consultation is recommended as disease-specific therapy (e.g., <span data-sememe-id=\"ObdIFo0\">tecovirimat</span>, IVIG) may be indicated.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>IV <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=pm0Lgg&anker=Z5a0cef096920d39da0f3cc2cbeb0fc9b\" data-learningcard-id=\"pm0Lgg\" data-anker=\"Z5a0cef096920d39da0f3cc2cbeb0fc9b\" data-section-id=\"DBX1100\" data-sememe-id=\"6WYjmL\">acyclovir</a> and inpatient management would be appropriate for disseminated <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mf0M52&anker=Z9c0f3c799bbad9d49380b5e5193c6bfc\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mf0M52\" data-anker=\"Z9c0f3c799bbad9d49380b5e5193c6bfc\" data-section-id=\"PpXWp_\" data-sememe-id=\"Dna1vO\">varicella-zoster virus</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Mf0M52&anker=Z9c0f3c799bbad9d49380b5e5193c6bfc\" data-learningcard-id=\"Mf0M52\" data-anker=\"Z9c0f3c799bbad9d49380b5e5193c6bfc\" data-section-id=\"PpXWp_\" data-sememe-id=\"Dna1vO\">VZV</a>) or disseminated <span data-sememe-id=\"yE1dyi0\">herpes simplex virus</span> (<span data-sememe-id=\"yE1dyi0\">HSV</span>), which can both present with widespread <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=_405NT&anker=Z7c5fd3823051fa560edec27fe227985f\" data-learningcard-id=\"_405NT\" data-anker=\"Z7c5fd3823051fa560edec27fe227985f\" data-section-id=\"-EXDy-\" data-sememe-id=\"tCaXF5\">vesicular lesions</a> and systemic symptoms, but mostly in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=x50Emg&anker=Z1af19ecc772907dd339670b5fb0e8b51\" data-learningcard-id=\"x50Emg\" data-anker=\"Z1af19ecc772907dd339670b5fb0e8b51\" data-section-id=\"h_XcL00\" data-sememe-id=\"P2YW3o\">immunocompromised</a> patients. This patient is previously healthy and has clinical features (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=iL0Jxg&anker=Z7b0bf382e960f8be4f9fccafce5ff227\" data-learningcard-id=\"iL0Jxg\" data-anker=\"Z7b0bf382e960f8be4f9fccafce5ff227\" data-section-id=\"2YWToP0\" data-sememe-id=\"66cjNW0\">generalized lymphadenopathy</a>) more consistent with an alternate diagnosis.</div>",
